A vintage-style illustration of an old wooden filing cabinet with its drawers partially open, revealing organized documents transforming into streams of golden butterflies that flutter upward and away. The cabinet sits in a warm, sepia-toned room with afternoon light streaming through a window, casting long shadows. Some butterflies carry tiny fragments of paper as they ascend toward an ornate antique mirror on the wall, which reflects not the room but a glimpse of a modern, organized digital landscape. The color palette features rich browns, amber, cream, and touches of deep burgundy, evoking a sense of transition and careful preservation during change.
